# UI/UX Guidelines

## Design Principles
- Clean, minimalist aesthetic
- Generous whitespace usage
- Professional color palette
- Dark mode support from start
- Mobile-first responsive design

## Component Structure
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Implement reusable Blade components
- Follow Livewire best practices
- Use Alpine.js for enhanced interactivity

## Key UI References
- **Linear**: Task-focused dashboard
- **Vercel**: Clean dashboard with dark mode
- **Craft**: Writing/reading experience
- **Stripe**: Form and settings pages

## Dashboard Design
- Hyper-focused primary dashboard
- Large, central card for active tasks
- Two prominent buttons: "I Completed This," "I Failed This"
- Clear, unambiguous interface

## Content Feeds
- Card-based layout for browsing content
- Uniform cards with key information
- Title, snippet, author, reactions
- Scannable format

## Forms
- Simple, single-purpose forms
- Avoid clutter
- Guide users through process
- Clear validation feedback

## Mobile Optimization
- Touch-friendly interface
- Responsive design
- Fast loading
- Offline capability where possible